James C. Rogers, CIMA®
President and Acting Regional Director, West Region
201-859-6158
jrogers@rooseveltinvestments.com
James Rogers joined Roosevelt Investments in 2005 as a Managing Director and the National Sales Manager responsible for client service and product distribution in institutional and intermediary channels. Mr. Rogers was promoted to President in 2013. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Rogers served as a Regional Director of Sales for the northeast-metro region with ING Investment Management. He has over 20 years of institutional sales experience and has held various sales management and financial advisory roles at NM Capital Management, a subsidiary of John Hancock Funds, and Merrill Lynch. Mr. Rogers earned a BA from Fairleigh Dickinson University, and a Certified Investment Management Analyst (CIMA) designation in 2003. He is a member of the Investment Management Consultants Association (IMCA) and currently holds a Series 7, 63 and 65 licenses.



Regional Director

Courtney John Bercini
Senior Vice President and Regional Director, Mid-America Region
(630) 235-1475
jbercini@rooseveltinvestments.com
John Bercini joined Roosevelt Investments in 2008 as Senior Vice President and Regional Director primarily responsible for sales coverage in the Great Lakes region. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Bercini was a sales representative with Eaton Vance, where he was instrumental in the development of the firm's separate account business and helped to introduce the Parametric Portfolio Associates Tax Managed Core Portfolio and Research Affiliates Fundamental Index Portfolio. He was also formerly the Midwest Regional Director for Regent Investor Services, the separate account division of Alliance Bernstein. Mr. Bercini earned a BS and MA from Western Michigan University, and currently holds Series 6, 7, 63 and 65 licenses.



Regional Director

Michael Miranda
Regional Director, Mid-Atlantic Region
646-452-6707
mmiranda@rooseveltinvestments.com
Michael Miranda joined Roosevelt Investments in 2011. He is the Regional Director primarily responsible for sales coverage in the Mid-Atlantic Region. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Miranda was an Internal Wholesaler at Smart Growth Mutual Funds and Director at SPA Exchange Traded Funds. Prior to that, he served on the Prudential Equities Institutional Sales Desk, worked at Pimco Equity Advisors, and prior to that Oppenheimer Capital. Mr. Miranda earned his B.B.A at Pace University and currently holds Series 7 and 63 licenses as well as Life and Health Insurance Licenses in the State of New Jersey.



Portfolio Management Liaison

Nainesh Shah, CFA
Portfolio Manager
Nainesh Shah joined Roosevelt Investments in 1994 and served on its domestic equity team as a senior securities analyst until he was promoted to Portfolio Manager in 2013. Mr. Shah is responsible for equity coverage of a broad spectrum of industries with a particular focus on the financial, communication and technology industries. He is also actively involved in the quantitative analysis employed in the firm's risk management process. A native of Bombay, he earned a bachelor's degree in Industrial Engineering from the University of Baroda, India, and an MBA in Finance from the Dalhousie University in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Mr. Shah received his CFA charter in 1997 and is a member of the New York Society of Securities Analysts.








Corie Gabriel
Tim Hermann, CFP®
