Corie Gabriel
Director of Private Client Group
Corie Gabriel joined Roosevelt Investments in 2008 as an Investment Counselor in the Private Client Group. Mr. Gabriel acts as a primary point of contact to the firm's individual investor clientele, responsible for all facets of client service. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Gabriel was a Senior Relationship Manager at Fisher Investments. He was also formerly a Financial Advisor and Retirement Planning Specialist at Morgan Stanley and Wachovia Securities, respectively. Mr. Gabriel earned a BS in Financial Services from The Pennsylvania State University.



Tim Hermann, CFP®
Vice President
							Senior Investment Counselor, Private Client Group
Tim Hermann joined Roosevelt Investments in 2009 as an Investment Counselor in the Private Client Group. In 2014, Mr. Hermann was promoted to Vice President and Senior Investment Counselor. Mr. Hermann acts as a primary point of contact to the firm's individual investor clientele, responsible for all facets of client service. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Hermann was a Senior Relationship Manager at Fisher Investments and was also formerly an Associate and Investment Banking Analyst at JPMorgan Chase & Co. Mr. Hermann earned a BS in Applied Economics and Management from Cornell University. Mr. Hermann is a Certified Financial Planner™ professional.



Sean Sokolowski
Investment Counselor, Private Client Group
Sean Sokolowski joined Roosevelt Investments in 2014 as an Investment Counselor in the Private Client Group. Mr. Sokolowski acts as a primary point of contact to the firm's individual investor clientele, responsible for all facets of client service. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Sokolowski was an Assistant Vice President and Senior Regional Consultant at AllianceBernstein. He earned his BS in Finance from the University of Delaware and currently holds his series 7 and 66 licenses.








Steven Weiss, Esq.



Steven Weiss, Esq.
General Counsel, Chief Operating Officer
Steven Weiss joined Roosevelt Investments in 2007 as the General Counsel, Chief Administrative Officer and Chief Compliance Officer responsible for all legal and compliance aspects for the firm. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Weiss was an attorney with Thelen, Reid, Brown, Raysman and Steiner LLP. He is currently an Adjunct Professor of Law at the Benjamin N. Cardozo School of Law in Manhattan. Mr. Weiss earned a BA in Political Science from Tufts University and a JD, cum laude, from the Benjamin N. Cardozo School of Law.








David Sheer
Karen DeArruda, CIPM®
Jeremy Bourgeois
Kevin Lafontaine



David Sheer
Co-Chief Executive Officer
David Sheer is the Chief Financial Officer of The Roosevelt Investment Group, Inc. responsible for the financial management and administrative oversight of the firm. Mr. Sheer was previously an executive member of the predecessor firm, Sheer Asset Management, Inc., where he managed all aspects of operations. He was instrumental in the establishment and development of the Roosevelt Investments operations center in Providence, RI, which was formed in 2005. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Sheer held various roles in client relations for Starwood Hotels & Resorts. He earned a BS in Psychology from Emory University and an MBA from Johnson & Wales University.



Karen DeArruda, CIPM®
Director of Operations
Karen DeArruda joined Roosevelt Investments in 2007 as the Operations Manager and in 2011 was promoted to Director of Operations. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Ms. DeArruda was the Back Office Manager for Taylor Investment Associates. She was also formerly the Financial Systems Manager for Freedom Capital, where she utilized and managed the Advent Software suite of products and oversaw portfolio administration, new accounts and trade settlement. In 2013, Ms. DeArruda earned the Certificate in Investment Performance Measurement (CIPM) designation.



Jeremy Bourgeois
Head Trader
Jeremy Bourgeois joined Roosevelt Investments in 2006 and has more than 15 years of industry experience, including an extensive trading background in domestic equities, foreign ordinary equities, domestic fixed income, and non-dollar denominated fixed income instruments. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Bourgeois served as a trader at John Hancock Advisors. He earned a BA in Finance from Bentley College.



Kevin Lafontaine
Assistant Trader
Kevin Lafontaine joined Roosevelt Investments in 2007 and has more than 12 years of industry experience, and is responsible for all aspects of the trade settlement process. Prior to joining Roosevelt, Mr. Lafontaine served as the Corporate Actions Manager at Investors Bank and Trust. He earned a BA in Finance from Salve Regina University.










